All routes and there endpoints are listed below.

### Users Routes

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Status |

| POST | /api/register | This endpoint allow users to register. Hash the password on store. | 201 |

| POST | /api/login | This endpoint allow users to login. Return JWT token on login. | 201 |

| PATCH | /api/user/id/reset | This endpoint allow users to reset the password identified by user id, providing the current password and new password in the body. | 204 |

### Restaurants Routes

| METHOD | ENDPOINT | DESCRIPTION | STATUS CODE |

| GET | /api/restaurants | This endpoint return a list of all available restaurants. | 200 |

| GET | /api/restaurants/id | This endpoint return the details of a specific restaurant identified by its ID. | 200 |

| GET | /api/restaurants/id/menu | This endpoint return the menu of a specific restaurant identified by its ID. | 200 |

| POST / PUT | /api/restaurants/id/menu | This endpoint allow the user to add a new item to a specific restaurants menu identified by it id. | 201 |

| DELETE | /api/restaurants/id/menu/id | This endpoint allow the user to delete a particular menu item identified by its id from a specific restaurant. | 202 |

### Orders Routes

| METHOD | ENDPOINT | DESCRIPTION | STATUS CODE |

| POST | /api/orders | This endpoint allow the user to place an order. | 201 |

| GET | /api/orders/id | This endpoint return the details of a specific order identified by its ID. | 200 |

| PATCH | /api/orders/id | This endpoint allow users to update the status of a specific order identified by its ID. | 204 |
